        <div class="content px-4 md:px-20 lg:px-44 mt-8 md:mt-16 mb-8 md:mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl uppercase font-bold text-black">
            Overview of phd program
          </h2>
          <div class="w-full h-[1px] bg-zinc-300 mt-2"></div>
          <h3 class="text-base md:text-lg mt-4 md:mt-5 leading-relaxed">
            IIIT Nagpur offers Ph. D programme under following categories
          </h3>

         <div>    
           <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">1. Industry Candidates:</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-10 mt-4">
                <li>Extern Candidate from Industry (EX-I)</li>
                <li>Intern Sponsored Candidate from Industry (IN-IS)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">2. Academic Institution(s) Candidates:</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-10 mt-4">
                <li>Extern Self-financed candidates from Academic Institutions (Ex-A)</li>
                <li>Intern Sponsored Candidate from Academic Institutions (IN-AS)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">3. Other Candidates:</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-10 mt-4">
                <li>Intern Self Sponsored Candidates (IN-U)</li>
                <li>Intern externally funded or sponsored or Project Staff Candidates (IN-ES)</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">The overall operation of the Ph.D. programme is governed by the Academic Regulations of the Institute. The students are required to refer to the PhD Rule Book for academic regulations and other details.</p>
            
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">Admission Modality</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">Admission to the Ph.D. programme is made once a year against the advertisement, which can be checked at <a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Click here</a>. Candidates have to apply through the online application form.</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">A candidate is normally admitted to the Ph.D. programme after passing his/her Ph.D. qualifying/entrance examination followed by an interview.</p>
           </div>
           <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">Application Procedure : </h2>
           <div class="pl-8">
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">The applications are to be filled in online mode with all relevant documents attached, and a separate hard copy of the same <strong>application filled Online must be sent by post along with documents</strong>. To avail of the online form, a Gmail account is essential.</p>
            <p class="mt-2 font-bold text-zinc-900">Applicants are advised to note that they have to submit an online application as well as send the hard copy to the Institute.</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">All applications which are not in the prescribed form, without relevant supporting enclosures, received after the last date, or without application fees will be outrightly rejected.</p>
           </div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-14">Examination Pattern:<h3>
            <div class="mt-7">
                <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Entrance Test:</h2>
                <p class="mb-4">The question paper for entrance test shall comprise of two sections.</p>
                
                <p class="font-normal"><span class="font-bold underline">Section-1</span> shall be common for all categories and would comprise of questions on General Ability and Communication Skills.</p>
                
                <p class="font-normal mt-4"><span class="font-bold underline">The Section-2</span> shall have questions based on the syllabus for respective categories as under:</p>
                
                <p class="mt-8 font-bold">For Candidates from Industry (EX-I & IN-IS):</p>
                <p>Basic Engineering Maths; Basic Programming and Engineering Knowledge and Skills; Engineering Logical Analysis, Arithmetic, Industry Standards.</p>
                
                <p class="mt-12 font-medium">FOR ALL REMAINING CATEGORY CANDIDATES (EX-A, IN-AS, IN-U, IN-ES)</p>
            </div>
            <div class="container  mt-20 pl-16">
                <table class="w-full border border-gray-800 bg-white">
                    <thead>
                        <tr class="bg-zinc-200">
                            <th class="border border-gray-800 px-12 py-8 text-left font-bold">Stream</th>
                            <th class="border border-gray-800 px-12 py-8 text-left font-bold">Syllabus</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="border border-gray-800 px-4 py-2 font-semibold">Electronics and Communication Engineering</td>
                            <td class="border border-gray-800 px-4 py-2">
                                <ol class="list-decimal pl-12">
                                    <li>Engineering Mathematics</li>
                                    <li>Networks</li>
                                    <li>Signals and Systems</li>
                                    <li>Electronic Devices</li>
                                    <li>Analog Circuits</li>
                                    <li>Digital Circuits</li>
                                    <li>Control Systems</li>
                                    <li>Communications</li>
                                    <li>Electromagnetic</li>
                                </ol>
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="border border-gray-800 px-4 py-2 font-semibold">Computer Science and Engineering & Information Technology</td>
                            <td class="border border-gray-800 px-4 py-2">
                                <ol class="list-decimal pl-12">
                                    <li>Engineering Mathematics</li>
                                    <li>Digital Logic</li>
                                    <li>Computer Organization and Architecture</li>
                                    <li>Programming and Data Structures</li>
                                    <li>Algorithms</li>
                                    <li>Theory of Computation</li>
                                    <li>Compiler Design</li>
                                    <li>Operating System</li>
                                    <li>Databases</li>
                                    <li>Computer Networks</li>
                                </ol>
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-20">
                <h1 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Presentation on Statement of Purpose (SoP):</h1>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
                    <li>All the candidates are required to attach a Statement of Purpose (SoP) in the format available in the <strong>Annexure – 2</strong> to the online soft copy as well as hard copy of the application.</li>
                    <li>Candidates applying under the category <strong>Industry Candidates (EX-I)/(IN-IS)</strong> are required to give a short presentation of maximum 5 slides specifying a brief of intended / targeted problems at the time of interview.</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-14 mb-4">Selection Process:</h2>
                <p>The PhD Admissions shall be on the basis of Entrance Test and Interview. The procedure shall be as follows:</p>
                
                <h3 class="text-md font-bold mt-4">Stage 1:</h3>
                <p>Entrance Test - Eligible candidates are required to appear physically at the Institute Permanent Campus for the Entrance Test to be held in the Computer Labs of the Institute.</p>
                <p><strong>Qualifying Score in the Test:</strong> The minimum qualifying score shall be a normalized score decided taking into account the number of candidates to be called for interview. But in no case it will be less than 40%. The normalization will be done by considering the top most score to be 100% and scaling the scores of other candidates accordingly.</p>
                
                <h3 class="text-md font-bold mt-4">Stage 2:</h3>
                <p>Interview – Candidates qualifying the Entrance Test shall be eligible to appear for Personal Interview through Offline Mode.</p>
                
                <h3 class="text-md font-bold mt-4">Stage 3:</h3>
                <p>Calculation of Combined Score – A Combined Score shall be calculated on the basis of score in Entrance Test, Score in Personal Interview and GATE.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-20">
                <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Qualification as under:</h2>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                    <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-gray-400 text-left">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="border border-gray-400 p-2" rowspan="2">Candidate Category</th>
                                <th class="border border-gray-400 p-2" rowspan="2">Total Marks</th>
                                <th class="border border-gray-400 p-2" colspan="3">Weightage Distribution</th>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="border border-gray-400 p-2">Entrance Test</th>
                                <th class="border border-gray-400 p-2">Interview</th>
